iversity Archives    Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Breadcrumbs    Home    Help     Get a student job in the library   The Library hires student employees for a variety of work and for shifts during all of the hours the buildings are open. Check the UIC Careers website for a list of currently open positions. For more information regarding student employment at UIC, please see the UIC Student Employment Office .      Undergraduate or graduate student positions  Chicago   Check UIC Careers or job boards at Daley Library.  Read the job description for a summary of the job, required skills and experience and work hours.  Follow the instructions in the posting for applying for the position.   Peoria, Rockford and Urbana  Contact your library for more information on their application processes and open positions.  Have questions? Contact the library’s Human Resources department at (312) 996-7353 or lib-hr@uic.edu.          Filter by Location    Chicago-Daley    Chicago-Health Sciences    Peoria-Health Sciences    Rockford-Health Sciences    Urbana-Health Sciences      Filter by Topic    Accessibility    Borrowing    Computers, Printing & Scanning    Copyright & Scholarly Publishing    Course Reserves    Electronic Resources    Library Accounts    Off-Campus Access    Requesting Materials    Research Help    Searching    Special Collections & University Archives    Study Spaces    Uncategorized    Writing, Style & Citations            Need help?  Contact a Librarian!                 Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations           Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Circulation  (312) 996-2724    Reference 